-- MIDI CLOCK SYNC  (alternative to the internal-clock TIMER block above)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
-- Drives the player from incoming MIDI clock (status byte 0xF8) instead of
-- the firmware timer.  Use this when Ableton (or any MIDI clock master) is
-- the tempo source.
--
-- Standard MIDI clock = 24 pulses per quarter note.  The compiled song
-- uses song.pulsesPerBeat (typically 4) per quarter note.  Ratio:
--   midiClocksPerPlayerPulse = 24 / song.pulsesPerBeat
-- For ppb=4 → 6 MIDI clocks per player pulse.
--
-- IMPORTANT: when running in MIDI-sync mode, do NOT also start the timer
-- (skip element_timer_start in INIT).  Otherwise the player will be driven
-- by both clocks and double-advance.
